</UL>

<HR>
<BR>
<H2>Conclusion</H2>
<BR>
     <P>In conclusion, when we mention the word "pirate", two
different versions of it come to our minds.  The first are
the ruthless and violent men on a ship who stole treasures
from other people hundreds of years ago.  The second thing
that comes to mind is a person that illegally duplicates
computer software without buying it.  It may be difficult to
draw a relationship from these two viewpoints, but the act
of either piracy is pretty much the same thing.  It is theft.
Both were and are illegal and both hurts the legitimate
owner.  In dealing with the piracy that occurs nowadays, many
attempts will be made in the future in trying to prevent
software piracy.  No one single solution will ever completely
stop computer piracy instantly.  However, if we look at the
different roots of piracy and try to tackle each problem one
at a time, I believe we can do the next best thing for our
future.</P>
